Me and my friend go to see if they were open.. it was about 945-50 at the time, the open sign wasn't on but the door was open. So we come back and she's still not all the way set up , the open sign wasn't on and she hardly spoke. It was really quiet inside the store and the employee didn't really communicate with me and my friend. The cookies were all out right near the register and when we went to pay for our food she ends up forgetting the cash register and goes into the walk-in and brings it out! <Date>1616842963180<//Date><Rate>3</Rate>< Review>
Pretty solid experience overall. Food was very good and tasted awesome! The service was quick and we didn't have to wait long to have our order taken and to receive our food. Ambience of the place is super chill and mellow and all the decor was dope. On the flip side though I had to ask 5 times to get my water but all our other drinks came out very quickly so I'm not really sure what was up with that. Another star docked for the water too because I never received a refill but other than that, I really enjoyed my experience here and will be coming again.< /Review>

< Review>
Good food at a good price. If you're familiar with Sohpia's Thai Food and Bar in Davis, you'll feel right at home here (and with a few extra bucks in your pocket!). <Rating>4< /Rating>< Review>
Wanted to check this place out for awhile. It's right across from Birdcage Target and the menu looked like what I would love. We went on Friday night. It was not busy. Order at the counter then they bring the food to your table. Our Food was very flavorful. I give it 5 stars. Service was 4 stars but it is the ambiance that was the downfall. I felt like I was in a fish bowl. The fluorescence lights in the office style T Bar ceiling in combination with a wall of windows next to our table gave us an uncomfortable dining experience. I would go back for lunch but not at night. It's too bad because the food is great.
I recommend for lunch</Review>

<Text>We recently moved to the area, but we've lived all over the country and we're always looking for good Mediterranean food. This place ranks up there as one of our favorites. We had the chicken and lamb wraps, Greek fries, and borscht (yes they have borscht on the menu!). The food was fresh and delicious, and the borscht (beet and cabbage soup) was to die for; not quite as good as grandma's, but excellent. Good prices for the amount of food you get, and fresh hummus and pita as an appetizer. Not to mention the wall of Armenian attractions and history cards on the table are pretty cool. <text>I finally tried this place out after driving past it numerous times en route to Target, Ulta, Michaels, etc. It‚Äôs actually a great location because hungry shoppers can duck in for a break and some delicious food. I loved it and will definitely be back! Details below.

Atmosphere: Casual, but welcoming and comfortable. Would like a bit more ‚ÄúArmenian flair‚Äù since the restaurant is Armenian. E.g. my favorite Persian restaurant in town plays Persian music and is heavily decorated with Persian swag‚Äîeating there is more than a meal, it‚Äôs an experience.

Service: friendly, attentive but not overbearing. You order at the counter and the food is brought to you. Our food came out quickly, but we ordered a wrap and a salad‚ÄîI would expect a longer wait if we ordered kebab.

Food: we had the Armenian salad, falafel wrap, and a piroshki. The Armenian salad was awesome‚Äîin my opinion, it totally trumps the Greek salad which I also love (it‚Äôs similar to a Greek salad).

The falafel wrap was amazing‚Äîit‚Äôs something I plan to get again. Everything was fresh and balanced well, from the falafel, to the pita, to the sauce. Perfection.

The piroshki‚Äîthis was the weak link for me. I felt that it was a little bland. It‚Äôs a potato mixture wrapped in a doughy exterior and fried. The potato mixture could have had more herbs and spice, but maybe this is traditionally eaten as a side with something else? Not sure, but it doesn‚Äôt stand well on its own. Note that the piroshki is also HUGE. The picture makes it seem small but it‚Äôs not.</text><Resp>{'time': 1528269010734, 'text': 'Thank you so much.'}<//Resp>< Rate>

<user_name>Walter Davis<//user_name>< time>
1516426380303</time>
<rating>5< /rating>< Review>
I bought an Infiniti at Carmax of Riverside. I was lucky that the clock needed repair because under the warranty I was sent to Infiniti of Riverside for the repairs. Jeremy Scheetz was the service consultant at Infiniti of Riverside. I was scared going to a dealership for service. Little did I know, it was the beginning of years of excellent service. I always got a fair price for my routine maintenance. From day one, Jeremy was efficient, friendly, prompt and thorough. He finds "points" for me in rewards programs that resulted in very low cost repairs. I was surprised. It was like having a family member in the service department. Last summer, my cancer flared up and I had to buy medication that took a lot of my money. I also got huge electric and water bills. It is 120 degrees in the summer where I live. Then, my air conditioner broke in my SUV. The part and repair was Very expensive and not covered by my warranty. Jeremy FOUND a special Infiniti program and my costs were cut in half! When Jeremy is not there, Mike is and he delivers high quality service as well. I have never seen a service team like the one at Infiniti of Riverside or had cars as reliable as my two Infinitis. I used to own BMWs and Mercedes...I will never stray away from Infiniti as long as they keep making great cars and provide high quality consultants like Jeremy.< /Review>

<UserId.>111281993519635536268</UserId.>< username>
Vicky Dimapasoc</username>
<Time>1618775750787< /Time>< Rate>
5<//Rate>
< review>
One of our bulbs burned out on this beautiful lighting fixture that we bought for our bathroom when we first moved into our home many years ago and looked for this certain size bulb everywhere with no luck. We were about to order from EBay (which I'd rather not do) and I remembered Lamps Plus from hearing a positive comment from one of our friends before. I called the Riverside store and had received a very professional and pleasant experience resulting in ordering the exact bulbs we needed. They arrived on the stated time and were packed beautifully with great care (just like I would have packed them). Overall I appreciated not having to deal with any problems for a change, which seems to be the case all to often anymore. I now plan to visit Lamps Plus to look for a couple new lamps once we start working on giving our family room a new look.</review>

Since it has a fuel station I plugged it into my phone and this was my stop on a 10 hour drive. I live in Lake Tahoe and was on my way to Los Angeles and beyond. Safeway is the only place I shop. We only have 3 markets in South Lake Tahoe, 2 Safeways and a Rayleys market. Its the better deal, I can rack up the rewards and use them for gas or groceries.<//Review>

<Time>1578460596317<//Time><Gmap_id>0x80910742be06787d:0x67a8edde86b73628</Gmap_id>< Text>
They have a really good bakery with fantastic donuts.  Lots of other goodies as well.  I also like their produce section.  They have good sales but otherwise, prices are a little high.  However their gas prices can only be beat by Costco.  Staff is always friendly and helpful.  Lines are usually not bad.  Can also get a great cup of coffee and free Wi-Fi.  They offer a seating area in order to enjoy these amenities and seems popular with the college kids. All in all, it's a store I go to about once a month and I recommend it anyone who hasn't tried them out.  Side note, they have a Fed ex pick up once a day and a cash center that offers lots of extras.< /Text>

The man working at the Deli, Ryan, is very slow and has no sense of urgency even when he had a line of 5 people to help. We (2 people) were in line for at least 10 minutes as he made sandwiches as slowly as possible. A lady finally came to help, but she was slow too. Ryan got to us before she did, so then we waited several minutes while he looked for tortillas, only for the tortillas to be frozen & not able to thaw for a long while; we couldn't get what we asked for. Huge waste of time, and the guy was incompetent. Then this safeway was out of packs of scones "for the rest of the week" when I asked, and had no single person sized fresh fruit cups stocked. Further, their Starbucks didn't have a publicly accessible microwave to warm things up in, and they messed up one of our iced coffees but we only noticed when we got on the road. Waste of $$$. What a horrible experience and a waste of time.< /Text>
